North Warren is a census-designated place[https://archive.today/20130217132746/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=42:4215384:4255520 2010 Census Interactive Population Search] located along the Conewango Creek in Conewango Township, Warren County in the state of Pennsylvania, United States.  The community is located to the north of the city of Warren.  As of the 2010 census the population was 1,934 residents. A notable institution located in North Warren is the Warren State Hospital.
